    <Folder>
      <name>Intelligence Summary</name>
      <Placemark>
        <name>AI Council Assessment</name>
        <styleUrl>#intel</styleUrl>
        <description>The synthesized intelligence assessment reveals a U.S. military posture characterized by heightened operational tempo and strategic concentration in key theaters, particularly the Western Pacific and Middle East. Carrier strike groups (CVN-70, CVN-76, CVN-68, CVN-73) and amphibious ready groups (LHA-6, LHD-8, LHD-2, LHD-4, LHA-7) are actively deployed in the Philippine Sea and South China Sea, participating in RIMPAC 2026 exercises and conducting freedom of navigation operations. This deployment pattern underscores a deliberate strategy to deter Chinese aggression while reinforcing alliances through multinational exercises. In the Middle East, USS Rafael Peralta (DDG-115) enforces a maritime blockade in the Gulf of Oman, reflecting U.S. commitment to countering Iranian proxy activities and maintaining regional stability. Logistical support is robust, with USNS Kanawha (T-AO-196) conducting underway replenishment in the Caribbean Sea and multiple tanker aircraft (K35R, B762) sustaining long-endurance missions. High-altitude ISR platforms (E3TF, FA6X) and strategic airlifters (C17, C30J) indicate sustained global mobility and surveillance operations. Training activity remains robust, with multiple T-38 trainers (TORCH03, COBRA29, KENT06) conducting routine exercises across the U.S., while VIP transport (A319) suggests high-level personnel movement in Europe. The data indicates a coordinated U.S. military strategy to maintain regional stability, counter adversarial actions, and strengthen allied interoperability, with particular emphasis on the Indo-Pacific and Middle East. The absence of major carrier deployments in the Atlantic suggests a prioritization of Pacific and Middle Eastern theaters, while in-port status for several West Coast carriers (CVN-71, CVN-72, CVN-74) indicates maintenance cycles rather than operational gaps. Overall, the military posture reflects a dynamic and proactive approach to global security challenges.</description>
        <Point>
          <coordinates>0,0,0</coordinates>
        </Point>
      </Placemark>
    </Folder>
